author: Scott Ellis
title: Five shows you shouldn't miss: October 16 - 22, 2015
text:
Dogs: Their Secret Life, SBS, Monday, 7.30pm. Photo: Janie Barrett 
The Beautiful Lie 
Sunday, ABC, 8.30pm
A reimagining of Tolstoy's classic Anna Karenina , with the love and intrigue transplanted to a wealthy Melbourne family. Australian drama at its best.
Advertisement Dogs: Their Secret Life 
Monday, SBS, 7.30pm 
Anyone who has ever left their dog home alone and returned to a disaster area will want to catch this fascinating look at why dogs act like they do.
800 Words 
Tuesday, Seven, 8pm 
One of the most successful Australian series right now, 800 Words continues to surprise, this week moving the focus to the kids and their struggle to fit in.
Fargo 
Wednesday, SBS, 8.30pm. 
He made us laugh in  Cheers , but as Ted Danson shows in season two of  Fargo , there's a lot more to this actor than meets the eye.
No Activity 
From Thursday, Stan
